Package: singleCellConservation
Title: Cross-Species Single-Cell Marker Conservation Analysis
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Cristal", "Villalba Silva", email = "your.email@uthscsa.edu", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Tools for testing cross-species conservation of cell-subtype
    marker genes from Seurat objects with a species metadata column.
    Implements a 4-step pipeline: (1) unfiltered FindConservedMarkers
    across subtypes, (2) classification into Conserved / Partially
    conserved / Species-specific / Not significant using per-species
    log2FC, p-value (raw or adjusted), and detection-rate thresholds,
    (3) pairwise Pearson correlation of mean expression across species,
    and (4) expression stability scoring via normalized SD of expression
    ranks. Originally developed for a cross-species tongue atlas
    (Human/Marmoset/Mouse) but generalized to any Seurat object with a
    subtype and species metadata column.
